                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-30v: Anaphora of Our Lady Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, Qǝddase Maryam Gwäs’a, ቅዳሴ፡ ማርያም፡. F<locus target="#1r">1r, </locus> and passim mention the owner, ሥህለ ማርያም, written in purple ink. F<locus target="#31r">31r, </locus>-70v: Canticle of the flower, Maḫletä Ṣǝge, ማሕሌተ፡ ጽጌ፡, arranged in a secondary hand for the days of the week: Wednesday (<locus target="#41">41, </locus>), Thursday (<locus target="#46">46, </locus>).  Grohmann, Marienhymnen, 46–321; Osvaldo Raineri, Codices Comboniani Aethiopici (Vatican City, 2000) 108f., no. 103; Täsfa Gäbrä Śǝlasse, ማሕሌተ፡ ጽጌ፡ ወሰቆቃወ፡ ድንግል። (Addis Ababa, 1964 A. M. = 1971/2). See also Fessehation Andemariam, “Mariology in the ‘Mahleta Sege’: Abba Giyorgis Gassičča’s ‘Hymn of the Flower,’” MA Thesis, Salesian Pontifical University (Rome, 1994). F<locus target="#71r">71r, </locus>-76v: Sword of Divinity, Säyfä Mäläkot, ሠይፈ፡ መለኮት፡, AbbCat 171, <locus target="#29v">29v, </locus>, Notice 104; AbbCat 186, <locus target="#104">104, </locus>, Notice 233; StrLin 47, f.88v. <locus target="#76v">76v, </locus>-92r: Image of Michael, Mälk‘a Mika’el, መልክአ፡ ሚካኤል፡. Répertoire 119. Incipit : ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ምስለ: ስመ: ልዑል: ዘተሳተፈ:. MG 290ff.  F<locus target="#92r">92r, </locus>-101r: Image of Gabriel, Mälk‘a Gäbra’el, መልክአ፡ ገብርኤል፡, incipit: ሰላመ: መልአክ: ገብርኤል: በላዕለ: ማርያም: ዘአዕረፈ:. Répertoire 246; MG 312ff. F<locus target="#101r">101r, </locus>-115v: Image of Saint George zä-Säläda Mogäs, መልክአ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ዘሰሌዳ፡ ሞገስ።  incipit: ሰላም: ለዝክረ: ስምከ: ዘሰሌዳ: ሞገስ: መጽሐፉ:  Répertoire 147.  F<locus target="#116r">116r, </locus>-132r: Image of Täklä Haymanot, Mälk‘a Täklä Haymanot, መልክአ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡. incipit: ሰላም: ለጽንሰትከ: ወለልደትከ: እምከርሥ:, Répertoire 211; MG 566ff. F<locus target="#132r">132r, </locus>-136v: Image of Gäbrä Mänfas Qǝddus, Mälk‘a Gäbrä Mänfas Qǝddus, መልክአ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡, Incipit: ሰላም: ለጽንሰትከ: መሠረተ: ነገር: ወውጣኔ:  Répertoire 196. MG 553ff. F<locus target="#132r">132r, </locus>-138v: Hymn to Jesus Christ, “O You Who Came Down from Heaven,” ኦ፡ ዘወረድከ፡ አምሰማይ፡, written in a later hand in blue ink. HTexte 20–7, <locus target="#34r">34r</locus>;  IES 75; EMIP 289.</summary>
